com.epoch.evals

Class Evaluator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.epoch.evals.Evaluator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AppConstants, EvalConstants, EvalImplConstants, XMLConstants

    public class Evaluator
extends Object
implements AppConstants, EvalConstants
    A generalized evaluator, with methods for submitting a response for evaluation and combining subevaluators' results into a single result to pass back to the front end.

      • isHumanGradingReqd

        public boolean isHumanGradingReqd()
                           throws ParameterException
        Determines whether human grading is ALWAYS required for this evaluator. Note that human grading may or may not be required if the human grading required evaluator is one of several subevaluators.
        Returns:
        true if the evaluator is simple and its sole subevaluator requires human intervention
        Throws:
        ParameterException - if there is no first subevaluator

      • matchResponse

        public OneEvalResult matchResponse(Response response)
                            throws ParameterException
        Determines whether a response satisfies this evaluator. Called from Question.java.
        Parameters:
        response - student's parsed response
        Returns:
        a OneEvalResult, which includes a boolean (true if the evaluator is satisfied). If the evaluator is satisfied, it may also contain a modified response or automatic feedback. If not, it may contain an error message. Complex evaluators will return automatic feedback if the last subevaluator of an OR expression to be satisfied generated the feedback, or if the first subevaluator of an AND expression generated it.
        Throws:
        ParameterException - if there is no first subevaluator

      • satisfiesRule

        public OneEvalResult satisfiesRule(int subevalNum,
                                   Response response)
        Determines whether a response satisfies one particular subevaluator. Called by CombineExpr.isSatisfied().
        Parameters:
        subevalNum - 1-based number of the subevaluator
        response - student's response
        Returns:
        a OneEvalResult, which includes a boolean (true if the evaluator is satisfied). If the evaluator is satisfied, it may also contain a modified response or automatic feedback. If not, it may contain an error message.
